Tower of Babel. Tower of Babel by Hendrick van Cleve at [Kunsthalle] Hamburg (1525-1580) (Photo Witt Library) When exactly was he in Italy? When was this picture painted? The Tower is round near a river, a Roman triumphal arch in front of it, classical details. In the foreground men working at stones like Bruegel, Vienna. It all looks more like based on Bruegel than the other way around.

column4: <content>Tower of Babel. Tower of Babel  by Hendrick van Cleve at [Kunsthalle] Hamburg (1525-1580) (Photo Witt Library) When exactly was he in Italy? When was this picture painted? The Tower is round near a river, a Roman triumphal arch in front of it, classical details. In the foreground men working at stones like Bruegel, Vienna. It all looks more like based on Bruegel than the other way around.</content>
<part_of.title>Towers of Babel. Reproductions. Towers of Babel by other Artists.</part_of.title>
